  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Ongoing violence and conflict has overwhelmed Sudans Darfur region since 2004 where an estimated 2 million people have fled their homes. The situation having deteriorated significantly since February 2014, resulted in displaced people requiring urgent assistance in the overcrowded Zamzam and Twila IDP camps.  JOAC granted Plan UK GBP 30,000 to help tackle the most pressing and immediate needs relating to water, sanitation and hygiene for 62,812 people.</narrative>
